			<div class="smallfont">
				&nbsp;<br />
<div>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103666" target="blank">Magelo Profile</a></div>

<div>Join Date: Jun 2003</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div><a href="#" onclick="return imwindow('icq', '128', 500, 450)"><img src="images/misc/im_icq.gif" alt="Send a message via ICQ to Savanna" border="0" /></a>   <a href="#" onclick="return imwindow('yahoo', '128', 400, 200)"><img src="images/misc/im_yahoo.gif" alt="Send a message via Yahoo to Savanna" border="0" /></a></div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>The thing with removing sleep from priest is it puts them back into a healer only role.  They wanted to give mages a spell to make them group friendly when I could see them adding chains back or something along those lines and keep the sleep on the priest.  I want to play a class with some versatility which is why I loved both the priest and warlock.  They were not classes you just sat and just pressed the same spells over and over.  They were very active classes.  You had something to add to a group but in more then just a single aspect such as healing only.  Yes, there are other things to the priest then heal like oh a dot, or a nuke here or there.  To me, sleep really added that extra umph to seperate from any priest/cleric class i've played in the numerous other games we've all played.   Also, sleep did help soloing as a priest.  I duo'd with my fiance a lot but there were many times I soloed and having the sleep to hold off an add in some areas was nice, not to mention for herbalism! <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" />    <br />
<br />
I, like most, will wait to see how this turns out with the new patch and we start playing again but I don't see priest holding my attention now.  The thought process of &quot;let's see what the new spells add&quot; doesn't do much for me as some of the new spells they have added are heals.  That just adds more of a healer role to them. <br />
<br />
Then again, we can all stop playing priest and go play paly, shaman or the druid to get some heals and actually have some versatility besides straight up healing.  <br />
<br />
I'm curious to see how many people actually enjoy the new changes and how many priests are around.  During testing, priests have never been that popular of a class compared to most so i'm curious to see the amount it drops by now without this added versatility.   <br />
<br />
I can see the tap thing being abused but at the same time really helping out the ks problem.  I've hated the ksing that has gotten worse as things have progressed and this is a needed change.  Whether it works the way they have set now or needs some tweaks, they do need something like this in place to say the least.<br />
<br />
Resting is an interesting concept and I can see some good but there is a LOT of protest going on against it and mainly by powerlvlers or those that play for long periods of time.  I would consider myself pretty hardcore at times but I go in spurts and I truely believe people need some breaks.  I know that some are going to flame me for that but god it doesn't hurt to get off your arse and heck go get some food or get out of the house for an hour or 2.  I, myself do play for hours on end and at times all weekend (yes i'm a addict, get a life type at times) so I can see both points.  Not sure what to think about the 8 hours thing yet.  That may be pushing it but some smaller breaks are not a bad thing.  /shrugs I dunno how this will effect the overall feel of the game yet though.  <br />
<br />
<br />
Looking forward to the new instances also <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" /> and also wanting to try out druid but let the rush of them begin since priest changes.<br />
<br />
edit : pedi, thinking alike on the chains back <br />
<br />
savvy</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
